defs.name: SendError
defs.docs: An error returned from the [`Sender::send`] method.

defs.name: Full
defs.docs:
The data could not be sent on the channel because it would require that the callee block to
 send the data.

defs.name: Disconnected
defs.docs:
This channel's receiving half has disconnected, so the data could not be sent. The data is
 returned back to the callee in this case.

defs.name: TrySendError
defs.docs: This enumeration is the list of the possible error outcomes for the [`try_send`] method.

defs.name: Timeout
defs.docs: This channel is currently full, but the receivers have not yet disconnected.

defs.name: Disconnected
defs.docs: The channel's receiving half has become disconnected.

defs.name: SendTimeoutError
defs.docs:
This enumeration is the list of possible errors that made [`send_timeout`] unable to return
 data when called. This can occur with bounded channels only.

defs.name: SelectSendError
defs.docs: An error returned from the [`Select::send`] method.

defs.name: RecvError
defs.docs: An error returned from the [`Receiver::recv`] method.

defs.name: Empty
defs.docs:
This channel is currently empty, but the senders have not yet disconnected, so data may yet
 become available.

defs.name: Disconnected
defs.docs:
The channel's sending half has become disconnected, and there will never be any more data
 received on it.

defs.name: TryRecvError
defs.docs:
This enumeration is the list of the possible reasons that [`try_recv`] could not return data
 when called. This can occur with both bounded and unbounded channels.

defs.name: Timeout
defs.docs:
This channel is currently empty, but the senders have not yet disconnected, so data may yet
 become available.

defs.name: Disconnected
defs.docs:
The channel's sending half has become disconnected, and there will never be any more data
 received on it.

defs.name: RecvTimeoutError
defs.docs:
This enumeration is the list of possible errors that made [`recv_timeout`] unable to return
 data when called. This can occur with both bounded and unbounded channels.

defs.name: SelectRecvError
defs.docs: An error returned from the [`Select::recv`] method.
